1. Create the new directory structure:
    > mkdir p5new
  under p5new, create the directories
	code
	config
	documentation
	input
	output
	run
	sumout
	tmp
   The CBP file storage system (as of 2009) is partitioned in to 'archive'
    and 'nobackup' sections.  The non-reproducible information should be on
    'archive' and the rest should be on 'nobackup'.  This can be done through
    symbolic links so that it looks like a cohesive file system.  To implement
    this, do the following:
  Under /bluefish/archive/modeling/p5new/>
  	md code config documentation input run sumout
  Under /bluefish/nobackup/modeling/p5new/>
 	md output tmp
  Back Under /bluefish/archive/modeling/p5new/>
   	ln -s /bluefish/nobackup/modeling/p5new/output output
   	ln -s /bluefish/nobackup/modeling/p5new/tmp tmp
  Back Under /bluefish/nobackup/modeling/p5new/>
	similar 'ln' statements for code config documentation input run sumout

2. Copy the entire code, config, documentation, and run directories
  ./p5old/code/> tar cf - . | (cd ../../p5new/code; tar xvf -)
     etc, DO NOT use the 'cp' command as it may damage the system

3. In the ./p5old/input/ directory:
    Selectively copy the datasets you want.  Not all will be needed.
    remember to use tar for the big data sets

4. you may recompile all code using
   ./p5new/code/src/compile_hspf_libs.csh
   ./p5new/code/src/compile_all.csh
 	especially if transferring machines

5. Make the rest of the directories using run/make_land_directories.csh

6. Change ownership 

